15 feared killed in plane crash in Siberia
MOSCOW: At least 15 people including 5 crew of a Russian Antonov An-24 aircraft are feared killed in a Siberian town, even as massive relief and rescue operations have been launched to search for the survivors. "At 23:10 IST at the time of landing the aircraft with 15 people on board on Krasnoyarsk-Igarka flight crashed 700 meters from the landing strip of Igarka airport," ITAR-TASS reported quoting Emergency Situations Ministry spokesperson Irina Andriyanova. The incident took place in Siberian Siberian town of Igarka in Krasnoyarsk Territory. However, quoting sources Interfax said there could be some survivors, as the rescue workers have launched relief operation.